SIMPLE: electrotonic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electrotonic
<hw>E*lec`tro*ton"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to electrical tension; --
said of a supposed peculiar condition of a conducting circuit during its
exposure to the action of another conducting circuit traversed by a
uniform electric current when both circuits remain stationary.</def>
<rj><au>Faraday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Relating to electrotonus;
<as>as, the <ex>electrotonic</ex> condition of a nerve</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electrotonize</ent>⟦br⟧
